HEADWORD: magnum opus
<hw>mag"num o"pus</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧g"n⟦ucr⟧m ⟦omac⟧"p⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A great work of art or
literature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The greatest work or achievement of a particular
artist, writer, or other individual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Inspired by this milieu, [Max Stirner] wrote his <qex>magnum
opus</qex> <it>The Ego and Its Own</it>, which was published in November
1844.</q> <rj><qau>Svein Nyberg (The Small Max Stirner Web Page, 1988
[https://web.archive.org/web/19981207014247/http://www.math.uio.no/~solan/stirner/stirner.html])</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magnus hitch</ent>⟦br⟧
